1
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:30,520
[DOG BARKING]

2
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,320
[DOG BARKING]

3
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,760
[SHOUTING IN GERMAN]

4
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:14,000
[ALARM SOUNDS]

5
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:15,440
AAH!

6
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:56,760
<i>ACHTUNG!</i>

7
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,520
THEY'RE HERE.

8
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,920
THEY'RE COMING, SIR.

9
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:29,400
HAND ME THOSE FILES
OVER THERE,

10
00:05:29,480 --> 00:05:30,960
WILL YOU, PLEASE?

11
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,280
COLONEL WALDRON,
YOU KNOW HERR ENDER.

12
00:05:57,800 --> 00:06:00,280
A DOCTOR FROM
THE SWISS RED CROSS.

13
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:03,000
OBERSTLEUTNANT STRAUSS.

14
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:06,080
MAJOR VON STEINER.

15
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:14,320
COLONEL WALDRON IS
THE SENIOR BRITISH OFFICER,

16
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:16,520
MAJOR ROSE, HEAD OF
THE INTELLIGENCE COMMITTEE,

17
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:18,360
WING COMMANDER SHURLOCK,

18
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:20,920
HEAD OF
THE ESCAPE COMMITTEE.

19
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,080
I THINK YOU'VE COME
TO INVESTIGATE

20
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,080
THE KILLING
OF MY OFFICER.

21
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,200
AN ACCIDENT.

22
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:26,760
I WOULD LIKE THE RED CROSS
TO SEE THE WHOLE CAMP--

23
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:28,640
YOUR SLEEPING QUARTERS,
MESS, TOILET--

24
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:31,200
AND SEE THAT YOU ARE
BEING TREATED WELL,

25
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:33,960
ACCORDING TO THE SPIRIT
OF THE GENEVA CONVENTION.

26
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:38,480
P.A.: [SPEAKING GERMAN]

27
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:44,200
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

28
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:45,480
COME ON.

29
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:48,200
P.A.: ALL PRISONERS
REPORT TO THE BARRACKS

30
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:50,600
FOR RED CROSS INSPECTION.

31
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:12,200
PLEASE, SIR, CAN
I HAVE MY BALL BACK?

32
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:32,480
<i>YOU ARE THE SPORT FUHRER?</i>

33
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:35,200
I'M COLBY.

34
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,200
COLBY?

35
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:38,160
THAT'S VERY FAMILIAR.

36
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,760
IT'S A COMMON NAME.

37
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:44,200
THEY'RE VERY
ENTHUSIASTIC.

38
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:45,640
NO BLOODY GOOD,

39
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:47,200
BUT VERY
ENTHUSIASTIC, YEAH.

40
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,640
DO YOU PLAY MATCHES?

41
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:51,520
OH, YEAH. WE HAVE
A LEAGUE, 4 DIVISIONS.

42
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:52,960
WE EVEN PLAY
INTERNATIONALS.

43
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:53,960
INTERNATIONALS?

44
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:54,920
YEAH.

45
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:56,400
ENGLAND, IRELAND,
SCOTLAND, WALES.

46
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:58,320
AH, YOU CALL THAT
INTERNATIONAL.

47
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,760
IT WOULD BE INTERNATIONAL

48
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,840
IF YOU PLAYED
AGAINST GERMANY.

49
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,280
WE'D MURDER YOU.

50
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,240
OH.

51
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:05,440
COLBY.

52
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:07,280
JOHN COLBY.

53
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:10,640
YES. WESTERN UNITED
IN ENGLAND.

54
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:12,240
THAT'S RIGHT.

55
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:15,440
IT'S A SHAME THE WAR
HAS ENDED YOUR CAREER.

56
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:17,360
INTERRUPTED.

57
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:19,120
LET'S HOPE SO.

58
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:51,400
[ENGINE STARTS]

59
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,760
THE COLONEL'S PROTEST

60
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:19,160
WILL BE A WASTE
OF BREATH, I'M AFRAID.

61
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,280
2 HEARTS.

62
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,680
IF WE DON'T KICK UP A STINK,

63
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:24,600
WE GIVE THE BLIGHTERS
PERMISSION TO DO IT AGAIN.

64
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:25,720
NO BID.

65
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,200
PASS.

66
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:29,880
COLBY, WHAT WERE YOU
TALKING TO JERRY ABOUT?

67
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:31,480
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

68
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:32,840
2 SPADES.

69
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,280
IT IS OUR BUSINESS.

70
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:37,160
YOU WERE SEEN CONVERSING
WITH THE ENEMY--

71
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,600
A MAJOR VON STEINER.

72
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,040
WHAT DID HE WANT?

73
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,560
HE RECOGNIZED ME.

74
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,440
AS WHAT? PASS?

75
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,400
PASS.

76
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:46,200
SO THE MAJOR'S
A FOOTBALL FAN?

77
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:47,640
ELEMENTARY,
MY DEAR SHURLOCK.

78
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:50,480
KARL VON STEINER PLAYED
FOR GERMANY IN 1938.

79
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:52,440
WHAT DID HE
SAY TO YOU?

80
00:09:52,520 --> 00:09:53,440
BUZZ OFF.

81
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,440
IN GERMAN?

82
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:55,440
YEAH.

83
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:57,240
SHH. I THINK
I'M GETTING SOMETHING.

84
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:59,960
Radio: MINISTER OF PROPAGANDA
IS WORKING TO EXTREMES

85
00:10:00,040 --> 00:10:02,360
TO DIVERT WORLD ATTENTION
FROM LOSSES IN NORTH AFRICA

86
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:05,400
AND THE REPORTED INHUMAN
TREATMENT OF THE PRISONERS

87
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:07,080
FROM EAST EUROPEAN NATIONS.

88
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:28,560
WHAT'S THE VERDICT
ON WILLIAMS?

89
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:31,280
A REGRETTABLE MISTAKE.

90
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:34,160
THE WHOLE BLOODY WAR'S
A REGRETTABLE MISTAKE.

91
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,280
I AGREE.

92
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,400
DO YOU?

93
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:39,280
WELL, YOU CAN
BELIEVE ME OR NOT.

94
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,720
IT'S NOTHING TO ME.

95
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,960
IF NATIONS COULD SETTLE
THEIR DIFFERENCES

96
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:44,400
ON THE FOOTBALL PITCH,

97
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:46,320
WOULDN'T THAT
BE A CHALLENGE?

98
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:49,200
HOW WOULD YOU
LIKE TO PLAY A GAME

99
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:52,120
<i>AGAINST A TEAM
FROM THE WEHRMACHT,</i>

100
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,160
A TEAM FROM
THE ARMY BASE NEARBY?

101
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:57,520
WHAT FOR, TO
SETTLE THE WAR?

102
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:58,960
UNFORTUNATELY, NO.

103
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:00,240
LET'S SAY...

104
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,520
FOR MORALE.

105
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,960
YOURS OR OURS?

106
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:04,080
FOR BOTH.

107
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:07,160
LIFE IN THIS PLACE
MUST BE VERY BORING.

108
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:12,880
WHAT SORT OF TEAM?

109
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,320
ARE THEY ANY GOOD?

110
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:15,760
I HAVEN'T
CHOSEN A TEAM.

111
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,200
IT'S JUST AN IDEA.

112
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:20,080
IT'S NOT AN ORDER.
YOU CAN'T MAKE US PLAY.

113
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:21,640
NO. IT'S
A CHALLENGE.

114
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:26,160
NAH. IT WOULD
BE A WASHOUT,

115
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,600
A COMPLETE WASHOUT.

116
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:28,880
WHY?

117
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,320
WELL, LOOK AT THEM.

118
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:32,720
LOOK AT THEM.
THEY'RE BLOODY USELESS.

119
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:35,120
I MEAN, LOOK
AT THOSE CLOTHES

120
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,560
AND BLOODY
GREAT BOOTS.

121
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:38,000
THEY'RE CHARGING
ABOUT THERE

122
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:39,920
LIKE A HERD
OF ELEPHANTS.

123
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,040
PLAY FOOTBALL?

124
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,960
THEY CAN HARDLY
STAND UP.

125
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:44,720
BOOTS
CAN BE SUPPLIED.

126
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:49,040
YOU MEAN PROPER GEAR--
SHIRTS, SHORTS?

127
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:51,920
NO, NO, NO, NO.

128
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,360
NO BLOODY GOOD.

129
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:55,760
THEY COULDN'T RUN
ABOUT FOR 90 MINUTES.

130
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,680
THEY'LL BE CHUCKING
THEIR GUTS UP.

131
00:11:57,760 --> 00:11:59,240
ALL RIGHT.
I'M SORRY.

132
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:02,160
UH, MAJOR.

133
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,800
I'D WANT, UH...

134
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:08,720
SPECIAL CONDITIONS,
SPECIAL RATIONS.

135
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:11,600
THE TEAM WOULD HAVE
TO LIVE TOGETHER,

136
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:13,040
EAT TOGETHER.

137
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:17,360
I'D WANT, UH, MEAT,
FRESH VEGETABLES,

138
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:18,800
EGGS...

139
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:19,920
BEER.

140
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,840
YOU'LL TALK
TO YOUR COLONEL?

141
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:23,760
NO MATTER
WHAT HE SAYS,

142
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:27,120
IF YOU COULD SUPPLY US
WITH ALL THAT STUFF,

143
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,800
YOU'D HAVE A GAME
OF FOOTBALL.

144
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,960
OH, WHICH
REMINDS ME--

145
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:32,880
IF IT'S CONFINED
TO OFFICERS,

146
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:34,320
I'M NOT
BLOODY PLAYING.

147
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:36,240
I WANT
A DECENT TEAM.

148
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:40,080
I WANT THE LADS...
FROM OVER THERE.

149
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:41,640
OK?

150
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,680
WE SHALL SEE.

151
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,200
OH, UH,
JUST A MINUTE.

152
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:55,080
RIGHT. ESCAPES.

153
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:57,680
WE'VE HAD ALL
THE USUAL REQUESTS,

154
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:59,960
BUT HERE'S A NEW ONE
YOU MIGHT LIKE.

155
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:02,160
PETER BAILEY
HAS A PLAN

156
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:04,600
TO POLE-VAULT
THE SOUTH FENCE.

157
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:07,480
GOD, WHAT WILL
THEY THINK OF NEXT?

158
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:09,760
OH, CHRIST. REFUSED.

159
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:10,720
ANYTHING ELSE?

160
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:13,280
NO, NO. LET'S
HAVE HATCH IN.

161
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:15,640
HATCH.

162
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,960
SORRY TO KEEP YOU WAITING.
YOU'RE AMERICAN?

163
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,720
MMM. ENLISTED
CANADIAN ARMY.

164
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,240
'38, TRANSFERRED
COMMANDOS.

165
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:24,600
HOW LONG HAVE
YOU BEEN WITH US?

166
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:26,520
SINCE DIEPPE.

167
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,960
HOW MANY ATTEMPTS?

168
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:29,880
2 ON THE WAY,
3 SINCE THEN.

169
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:31,960
TIME BEFORE LAST,
I GOT TO STUTTGART.

170
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:34,080
HOW'S THIS ONE
GOING?

171
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:36,000
SIR, EVERYTHING
DEPENDS ON THE FACT

172
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:38,400
THAT SOME GOONS DON'T PATROL
WHEN WE'RE SHOWERING.

173
00:13:38,440 --> 00:13:40,040
UH, SOME OF THEM?

174
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:41,480
YES, LIKE HANS
AND ANTON.

175
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:43,360
AT LEAST ONE
SHOULD BE OUTSIDE

176
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,800
WALKING
BACK AND FORTH,

177
00:13:44,840 --> 00:13:47,400
BUT THEY KNOW WE'RE
INSIDE HAVING A SHOWER.

178
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:49,880
SO THEY COME INSIDE,
LEAN AGAINST THE DOOR,

179
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:51,240
HAVE A SMOKE
IF THEY CAN BUM ONE.

180
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:53,920
IF SOMEBODY WENT MISSING,
THEY WOULDN'T REPORT IT.

181
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:54,880
WHY NOT?

182
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:56,320
THEY'D THINK
THEY'D MISCOUNTED

183
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,960
AND LEAVE IT
UNTIL ROLL CALL.

184
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:00,160
IF YOU'D COVER
FOR ME AT ROLL CALL,

185
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,920
I COULD BE GONE
FOR DAYS.

186
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:04,080
WAIT A MINUTE. YOU'RE
GOING TOO FAST FOR ME.

187
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:05,480
HOW ARE YOU GOING TO GET
OUT OF THE WASH HOUSE?

188
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:07,680
THERE'S A VENT
IN THE SHOWER ROOM.

189
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:09,840
IT LEADS INTO A
STOREROOM OR SOMETHING.

190
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:11,120
IT MUST HAVE BEEN
BUILT AS A LAVATORY

191
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,360
TO MATCH THE ONE
ON THE GERMAN SIDE.

192
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:15,200
IF I CAN GET IN
AND PICK THE LOCK...

193
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:17,000
YOU'D BE BACK IN THE ENCLOSURE
WHERE YOU STARTED.

194
00:14:17,080 --> 00:14:19,760
BUT I'D BE ALL ALONE.
THERE'S NO ONE THERE.

195
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,120
NOW, I COULD
GET ONTO THE ROOF,

196
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:22,560
GO UNDERNEATH
THE BARBED WIRE,

197
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,960
AND DROP INTO
THE GERMAN COMPOUND.

198
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,000
NAKED?

199
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:29,360
AND, UH, HOW
ARE YOU PLANNING

200
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:32,320
TO GET OUT OF THE GERMAN
COMPOUND NAKED?

201
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:34,920
I'VE GOT 5 OR 6 IDEAS.

202
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,600
SHALL WE DISCUSS THEM?

203
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:39,880
YES.

204
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:48,320
COLBY INSISTED ON
PLAYING THE OTHER RANKS

205
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:50,000
AGAINST THE BEST
OF THE OFFICERS.

206
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,760
WHAT'S THE IDEA
BEHIND THAT?

207
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:55,320
I SUPPOSE HE WANTS TO PICK
THE BEST TEAM POSSIBLE.

208
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:58,640
I DON'T THINK HE'S QUITE
GOT THE POINT, HAS HE?

209
00:14:58,680 --> 00:15:02,160
TELL HIM TO COME AND
SEE ME, WILL YOU?

210
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:07,160
OH!
OH!

211
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,600
WELL DONE, SON.

212
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:10,040
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

213
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:11,160
SID ARMOR.

214
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:13,720
HOW'D YOU LIKE DOUBLE
RATIONS FOR A MONTH?

215
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:16,120
WHOSE MOTHER DO YOU
WANT ME TO STRANGLE?

216
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,200
WELCOME ABOARD.

217
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:20,440
OK, I'M READY
TO SIGN UP.

218
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,040
SIGN UP, HATCH.

219
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:31,160
TACKLE HIM!
TACKLE HIM!

220
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,120
GOAL!

221
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:33,080
NICE SHOT.

222
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,200
THANKS, COLBY.

223
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:35,960
IT'S NOT LIKE PLAYING
FOR MANCHESTER,

224
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:38,200
BUT IT'S BETTER THAN
NOT PLAYING AT ALL.

225
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:39,160
WELCOME ABOARD.

226
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,120
WHAT ABOUT ME?

227
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:41,560
GET OUT THERE.

228
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,000
WHAT ABOUT ME?

229
00:15:43,040 --> 00:15:44,560
GET OUT THERE
AND PLAY.

230
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:47,920
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

231
00:15:47,960 --> 00:15:49,800
THE MAP OF MARBURG
IS FROM AN OLD GUIDEBOOK,

232
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:51,240
BUT IT'S RELIABLE,
I SHOULD HOPE.

233
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,920
THERE'S A FAST TRAIN
TO COLOGNE

234
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:55,120
AT 5:33
EVERY SATURDAY.

235
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:58,000
UNDER THE MAP IS
A SKETCH OF THE STADIUM

236
00:15:58,040 --> 00:16:00,920
WITH EXITS, PERSPECTIVES,
AND CHANGING ROOMS.

237
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:04,080
COLONEL...WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

238
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:07,000
I'M TALKING ABOUT
YOUR ESCAPE, COLBY.

239
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:12,920
MY ESCAPE?

240
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:15,800
YES, OF COURSE.

241
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:17,240
THE WHOLE TEAM,
IF POSSIBLE.

242
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:19,160
WHAT ABOUT THE LORRY THAT'S
TAKING YOU TO THE MATCH?

243
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:20,880
YOU COULD LOOSEN
THE FLOORBOARDS ON THE WAY IN

244
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:22,320
AND DROP OUT
ON THE WAY BACK.

245
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:25,560
YOU STICK TO SCROUNGING,
AND I'LL STICK TO FOOTBALL.

246
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:27,800
