01:04:49,920 --> 01:04:52,520
TO SHOW THE OTHER PRISONERS
YOU'RE NOT A SUCCESS.

985
01:04:54,000 --> 01:04:56,400
YOU'VE GOT ALL
THE ANSWERS, DON'T YOU?

986
01:04:56,480 --> 01:04:57,640
YES.

987
01:04:59,040 --> 01:05:01,800
MISTER, YOU WILL
LEAVE TOMORROW.

988
01:05:04,080 --> 01:05:04,960
TOMORROW.

989
01:05:05,040 --> 01:05:06,120
YES. TOMORROW.

990
01:05:10,000 --> 01:05:12,520
THIS FRIGGING
SOCCER GAME...

991
01:05:13,520 --> 01:05:14,880
<i>ALLONS-Y.</i>

992
01:05:17,440 --> 01:05:19,280
I'LL LEAVE YOU MY PAPERS.

993
01:05:19,360 --> 01:05:20,880
THEY'RE PRETTY GOOD.

994
01:05:20,960 --> 01:05:25,200
I'M SURE SOMEBODY WILL
BE ABLE TO USE THEM,

995
01:05:25,280 --> 01:05:26,360
ALL RIGHT?

996
01:06:08,960 --> 01:06:10,080
WELL...

997
01:06:11,120 --> 01:06:12,320
HE'S BACK.

998
01:06:16,600 --> 01:06:17,520
<i>SCHNELL.</i>

999
01:06:17,600 --> 01:06:19,600
OH, THANK YOU.
THANK YOU.

1000
01:06:20,480 --> 01:06:22,520
[CHEERING]

1001
01:06:25,280 --> 01:06:26,600
COME ON.

1002
01:06:28,160 --> 01:06:29,320
MARCH, MARCH.

1003
01:06:31,080 --> 01:06:33,840
SO, OUR HATCH
KNOWS HIS MYTHOLOGY.

1004
01:06:33,920 --> 01:06:35,640
WHAT DOES IT MEAN?

1005
01:06:35,680 --> 01:06:37,280
MERCURY...

1006
01:06:37,320 --> 01:06:40,040
MESSENGER OF THE GODS.

1007
01:06:40,120 --> 01:06:41,280
NO FLIES ON ROSIE.

1008
01:06:41,320 --> 01:06:42,560
NEWS, EH?

1009
01:06:42,600 --> 01:06:45,440
HOW DO WE FIND OUT
WHAT IT IS?

1010
01:06:45,480 --> 01:06:47,080
GOOD QUESTION.

1011
01:06:53,240 --> 01:06:56,040
WE SENT HIM TO PARIS
ON YOUR BEHALF,

1012
01:06:56,120 --> 01:06:58,480
YOURS AND THE TEAM'S.

1013
01:06:59,720 --> 01:07:00,680
COLONEL...

1014
01:07:00,760 --> 01:07:03,560
I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

1015
01:07:03,640 --> 01:07:06,920
WE SENT HIM TO PARIS
TO ARRANGE YOUR ESCAPE.

1016
01:07:07,000 --> 01:07:08,840
HATCH DID THAT FOR YOU?

1017
01:07:08,920 --> 01:07:10,280
NO. FOR YOU.

1018
01:07:10,360 --> 01:07:11,560
WE COULD ARGUE
ABOUT THAT.

1019
01:07:11,640 --> 01:07:13,440
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

1020
01:07:13,520 --> 01:07:16,320
NO POINT UNLESS HE MANAGED
TO ARRANGE SOMETHING.

1021
01:07:16,400 --> 01:07:18,720
HE APPEARS TO HAVE
BEEN SUCCESSFUL.

1022
01:07:18,800 --> 01:07:21,040
SNAG IS,
HE CAN'T TELL US.

1023
01:07:21,120 --> 01:07:22,880
HE'S IN THE COOLER
UNTIL AFTER THE MATCH.

1024
01:07:22,920 --> 01:07:25,600
YOU'LL HAVE TO GET HIM
OUT OF THERE, WON'T YOU?

1025
01:07:25,680 --> 01:07:26,600
EXCUSE ME.

1026
01:07:26,680 --> 01:07:29,280
I HAVE
A TRAINING SESSION.

1027
01:07:29,360 --> 01:07:30,880
JUST A MINUTE. COLBY.

1028
01:07:30,920 --> 01:07:32,840
I KNOW YOU WANTED
TO PLAY

1029
01:07:32,920 --> 01:07:35,000
FOR THE SAKE OF
THOSE EASTERN EUROPEANS.

1030
01:07:35,040 --> 01:07:36,160
I ADMIRE YOU.

1031
01:07:36,200 --> 01:07:39,320
WE BOTH KNOW YOU'LL RISK
A COURT-MARTIAL FOR THIS

1032
01:07:39,360 --> 01:07:40,480
AFTER THE WAR.

1033
01:07:40,520 --> 01:07:41,920
WHAT HAVE
YOU ACCOMPLISHED?

1034
01:07:41,960 --> 01:07:44,000
GIVEN THEM A COUPLE
OF WEEKS OF LIFE?

1035
01:07:44,040 --> 01:07:45,080
WHAT HAPPENS TO THEM

1036
01:07:45,120 --> 01:07:46,840
AFTER YOUR MATCH
IS OVER?

1037
01:07:46,880 --> 01:07:49,320
FOR THE SAME REASON
YOU WANTED TO PLAY,

1038
01:07:49,400 --> 01:07:52,040
YOU MUST ESCAPE...
IF YOU CAN.

1039
01:07:52,120 --> 01:07:55,680
WHAT CAN I DO? I CAN'T
GET HIM OUT OF THERE.

1040
01:07:55,720 --> 01:07:59,040
HATCH IS OFFICIALLY
YOUR TRAINER, ISN'T HE?

1041
01:07:59,120 --> 01:08:01,440
VON STEINER AND
THE CAMP COMMANDANT

1042
01:08:01,520 --> 01:08:03,400
WON'T BUY THAT ONE.

1043
01:08:03,480 --> 01:08:06,040
I HAVE TO THINK
OF SOMETHING ELSE.

1044
01:08:21,080 --> 01:08:22,120
CRAZY YANK.

1045
01:08:32,800 --> 01:08:35,080
YOU, COLONEL WALDRON,
AND MAJOR ROSE

1046
01:08:35,160 --> 01:08:36,520
WILL TRAVEL TO PARIS

1047
01:08:36,600 --> 01:08:39,400
ALONG WITH OTHER SENIOR
OFFICERS FROM VARIOUS CAMPS

1048
01:08:39,480 --> 01:08:41,000
TO REPRESENT
YOUR COUNTRIES.

1049
01:08:42,080 --> 01:08:43,480
I WON'T DO IT.

1050
01:08:43,520 --> 01:08:45,480
YOU HAVE NO CHOICE.

1051
01:08:45,560 --> 01:08:46,920
THEN I'LL TRAVEL,

1052
01:08:47,000 --> 01:08:50,080
BUT I WON'T
REPRESENT ANYTHING.

1053
01:08:50,120 --> 01:08:52,280
YOU WILL BE SEEN.

1054
01:08:54,240 --> 01:08:56,680
THE TEAM WILL BE READY
TO TRAVEL

1055
01:08:56,760 --> 01:08:58,520
AT MIDDAY ON THURSDAY.

1056
01:08:58,560 --> 01:09:01,240
FURTHER ARRANGEMENTS
WILL BE ANNOUNCED LATER.

1057
01:09:01,280 --> 01:09:03,360
ONE OF MY MEN IS IN
THE PUNISHMENT BLOCK,

1058
01:09:03,440 --> 01:09:04,400
IN SOLITARY.

1059
01:09:04,480 --> 01:09:07,200
I'LL GIVE YOU A TRAINER.
YOU DON'T NEED HIM.

1060
01:09:07,280 --> 01:09:08,600
HATCH IS MY GOALKEEPER.

1061
01:09:08,640 --> 01:09:11,600
THE AMERICAN? NO.

1062
01:09:11,680 --> 01:09:13,520
TONY LEWIS
IS YOUR GOALKEEPER.

1063
01:09:13,600 --> 01:09:14,800
HE'S BROKEN HIS ARM.

1064
01:09:18,560 --> 01:09:20,160
WHEN DID THIS HAPPEN?

1065
01:09:20,240 --> 01:09:21,120
THIS MORNING.

1066
01:09:21,200 --> 01:09:22,560
PUT SOMEONE ELSE
IN GOAL.

1067
01:09:22,640 --> 01:09:24,480
HATCH IS MY BEST MAN.

1068
01:09:24,560 --> 01:09:27,640
I THOUGHT THE IDEA
WAS TO GIVE US A CHANCE.

1069
01:09:27,680 --> 01:09:29,440
THIS IS THE IDEA.

1070
01:09:33,680 --> 01:09:37,280
IF THE CAMP DOCTOR
VERIFIES THIS BROKEN ARM,

1071
01:09:37,360 --> 01:09:39,480
YOU MAY
HAVE THE AMERICAN.

1072
01:09:39,520 --> 01:09:40,840
THANK YOU.

1073
01:09:45,680 --> 01:09:47,200
WELL, TONY...

1074
01:09:49,440 --> 01:09:52,720
TRY AND MAKE IT
A CLEAN BREAK, WILL YOU?

1075
01:09:52,800 --> 01:09:53,760
I'LL TRY.

1076
01:09:53,840 --> 01:09:57,600
I WON'T EVEN GET TO
SEE THE GAME, WILL I?

1077
01:09:57,680 --> 01:09:59,200
SIT ON THE BED.

1078
01:10:00,560 --> 01:10:02,880
PUT YOUR ARM
BETWEEN THOSE TWO.

1079
01:10:02,960 --> 01:10:04,000
OK.

1080
01:10:21,920 --> 01:10:23,040
AAH!

1081
01:10:23,120 --> 01:10:24,880
[MOANING]

1082
01:11:34,640 --> 01:11:36,080
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

1083
01:11:36,160 --> 01:11:37,040
<i>OUI, MONSIEUR.</i>

1084
01:11:37,120 --> 01:11:38,720
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

1085
01:12:06,320 --> 01:12:07,520
<i>OUI, MONSIEUR.</i>

1086
01:12:07,600 --> 01:12:08,640
<i>GUT.</i>

1087
01:12:25,200 --> 01:12:28,720
COLBY, I DON'T KNOW HOW
TO PLAY THIS GAME,

1088
01:12:28,760 --> 01:12:31,600
SO WHERE DO I STAND
FOR THE CORNER KICK?

1089
01:12:31,680 --> 01:12:32,880
WHAT?

1090
01:12:32,920 --> 01:12:34,560
I'M NOT GOOD
AT THE GAME.

1091
01:12:34,640 --> 01:12:37,760
WHERE DO I STAND
FOR A CORNER KICK?

1092
01:12:37,840 --> 01:12:39,920
GO TO SLEEP, HATCH.

1093
01:13:06,360 --> 01:13:07,920
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

1094
01:14:02,520 --> 01:14:03,760
<i>KOMMEN SIE AUS.</i>

1095
01:14:07,800 --> 01:14:09,200
<i>FOLGEN SIE MIR.</i>

1096
01:15:21,240 --> 01:15:23,040
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

1097
01:15:29,560 --> 01:15:31,600
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

1098
01:16:22,880 --> 01:16:25,760
[BROADCASTING
IN GERMAN]

1099
01:17:48,640 --> 01:17:49,520
COLBY.

1100
01:17:49,600 --> 01:17:50,480
WHAT?

1101
01:17:50,560 --> 01:17:53,520
WHERE DO I STAND
FOR A CORNER KICK?

1102
01:17:54,880 --> 01:17:58,640
THE FAR POST,
FACING THE BALL.

1103
01:17:59,800 --> 01:18:01,040
THANKS.

1104
01:18:01,120 --> 01:18:04,840
FOR A WHILE, I THOUGHT YOU
WERE KEEPING IT A SECRET.

1105
01:18:22,280 --> 01:18:24,360
[BAND PLAYS]

1106
01:18:44,160 --> 01:18:47,000
<i>Announcer:
MESDAMES ET MESSIEURS...</i>

1107
01:18:48,120 --> 01:18:50,120
[INTRODUCING PLAYERS
IN FRENCH]

1108
01:19:01,200 --> 01:19:03,200
[APPLAUSE]

1109
01:19:58,680 --> 01:20:02,600
<i>[BAND PLAYS
DEUTSCHLAND UBER ALLES]</i>

1110
01:21:01,000 --> 01:21:03,840
A HEARTY WELCOME TO ALL
OUR LISTENERS IN ENGLAND.

1111
01:21:03,880 --> 01:21:05,760
THERE'S A FEW MINUTES TO GO

1112
01:21:05,800 --> 01:21:08,040
BEFORE THE KICKOFF
OF THIS HISTORIC MATCH.

1113
01:21:08,120 --> 01:21:09,960
THIS GREAT CROWD OF 50,000

1114
01:21:10,040 --> 01:21:12,760
REALLY HAS SOMETHING
TO LOOK FORWARD TO

1115
01:21:12,800 --> 01:21:14,640
DURING THE NEXT
90 MINUTES.

1116
01:21:14,720 --> 01:21:17,080
TO ENSURE FAIR PLAY
AND GOOD SPORTSMANSHIP,

1117
01:21:17,120 --> 01:21:19,000
THE GERMAN ORGANIZERS
PICKED A NEUTRAL

1118
01:21:19,040 --> 01:21:20,440
TO REFEREE THE MATCH.

1119
01:21:20,480 --> 01:21:22,840
AND HE IS NOW READY
FOR THE TOSS OF THE COIN.

1120
01:21:22,880 --> 01:21:23,840
HEADS.

1121
01:21:23,920 --> 01:21:26,720
THE WINNER WILL CHOOSE
TO KICK OFF OR DEFEND,

1122
01:21:26,800 --> 01:21:29,600
BUT WILL PROBABLY CHOOSE
TO PLAY TOWARD THE EAST GOAL

1123
01:21:29,680 --> 01:21:31,840
WITH THE WIND
IN HIS FAVOR.

1124
01:21:31,880 --> 01:21:34,160
THE ALLIES WILL KICK OFF
THIS GREAT EVENT.

1125
01:21:34,240 --> 01:21:36,360
I TELL YOU,
YEARS FROM NOW,

1126
01:21:36,440 --> 01:21:38,280
MEN WILL SAY
OF THIS GAME,

1127
01:21:38,360 --> 01:21:39,640
"DID IT HAPPEN?"

1128
01:21:39,680 --> 01:21:42,320
I TELL YOU IN THE LISTENING
AUDIENCE TODAY,

1129
01:21:42,400 --> 01:21:43,680
<i>IT IS HAPPENING.</i>

1130
01:21:43,760 --> 01:21:45,600
WE'RE ALL WITNESS
TO AN OCCASION

1131
01:21:45,680 --> 01:21:47,000
LONG TO BE REMEMBERED,

1132
01:21:47,040 --> 01:21:49,560
NOT AS PROPAGANDA,
AS SOME WOULD SAY,

1133
01:21:49,600 --> 01:21:52,120
BUT AS A MAGNIFICENT
SPORTING SPECTACLE.

1134
01:22:02,240 --> 01:22:04,000
HATCH, HATCH.

1135
01:22:05,400 --> 01:22:07,400
HATCH, HATCH.
HALFTIME, HALFTIME.

1136
01:22:07,480 --> 01:22:09,160
ALL RIGHT. THANKS.

1137
01:22:09,240 --> 01:22:10,840
WHAT DID HE SAY?

1138
01:22:10,880 --> 01:22:13,400
ALL RIGHT,
IT'S ON FOR HALFTIME.

1139
01:22:22,160 --> 01:22:23,600
HERE'S TO VICTORY.

1140
01:22:23,680 --> 01:22:25,440
<i>VICTOIRE!
VICTOIRE!</i>

1141
01:22:25,520 --> 01:22:28,120
<i>VICTOIRE!
VICTOIRE!</i>

1142
01:22:29,880 --> 01:22:31,240
COME ON, LOOK ALIVE!

1143
01:22:31,320 --> 01:22:33,280
LET'S GO! LET'S PLAY BALL!

1144
01:22:33,360 --> 01:22:34,720
PLAY HARD, HUH?

1145
01:22:34,800 --> 01:22:36,880
LET'S PLAY HARD.

1146
01:22:38,640 --> 01:22:41,040
ARMOR KICKS OFF
FOR THE ALLIES,

1147
01:22:41,120 --> 01:22:42,480
AND THE GAME HAS BEGUN.

1148
01:22:42,560 --> 01:22:44,880
YOU'D HAVE A JOB
GETTING 22 BETTER PLAYERS

1149
01:22:44,960 --> 01:22:47,360
THAN ARE OUT THERE
ON THE PITCH RIGHT NOW.

1150
01:22:47,400 --> 01:22:49,200
THE ALLIES
ARE PLAYING IT COOL.

1151
01:22:56,000 --> 01:22:56,880
VERY CLOSE.

1152
01:22:56,960 --> 01:22:58,200
VERY CLOSE.

1153
01:22:58,240 --> 01:23:01,080
THE BALL IS BACK IN PLAY
BY SCHMIDT,

1154
01:23:01,120 --> 01:23:02,720
GERMANY'S LEGENDARY
GOALKEEPER.

1155
01:23:02,760 --> 01:23:05,760
REINHART...
REINHART TO BECKER...

1156
01:23:05,840 --> 01:23:07,520
TO BAUMANN, NUMBER 4.

1157
01:23:07,560 --> 01:23:08,960
FORWARD NOW TO BRANDT.

1158
01:23:09,000 --> 01:23:11,480
BACK TO ALBRECHT,
NUMBER 11.

1159
01:23:16,160 --> 01:23:18,560
WATCH MY BACK!
WATCH MY BACK!

1160
01:23:23,280 --> 01:23:24,560
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1161
01:23:27,360 --> 01:23:28,920
HERE'S YOUR
CORNER KICK, HATCH.

1162
01:23:30,400 --> 01:23:31,800
GUYS, HELP ME OUT.

1163
01:23:31,840 --> 01:23:33,240
DEFEND
THAT GOAL POST.

1164
01:23:34,720 --> 01:23:36,600
WATCH HIM THERE.
WATCH HIM.

1165
01:23:37,880 --> 01:23:39,680
WATCH IT.
WATCH HIM THERE.

1166
01:23:45,920 --> 01:23:47,400
HEADS UP! I GOT IT!

1167
01:23:48,520 --> 01:23:50,200
IT'S A GOAL!

1168
01:23:53,000 --> 01:23:54,320
GERMANY 1, ALLIES NIL.

1169
01:23:59,720 --> 01:24:01,920
AND LISTEN
TO THAT APPLAUSE!

1170
01:24:02,000 --> 01:24:02,920
[APPLAUSE]

1171
01:24:03,000 --> 01:24:04,920
THE CROWD IS GOING WILD.

1172
01:24:08,520 --> 01:24:09,920
TAKE IT EASY.
YOU'RE TIGHT AS A DRUM.

1173
01:24:09,960 --> 01:24:11,560
JUST GET ME
TO HALFTIME.

1174
01:24:11,640 --> 01:24:13,560
DON'T GET PULLED
OFF YOUR LINE.

1175
01:24:21,800 --> 01:24:23,320
THAT'S A FOUL!

1176
01:24:36,640 --> 01:24:38,080
WATCH IT BACK THERE.

1177
01:24:46,480 --> 01:24:47,920
GOAL!
GOAL!

1178
01:24:48,000 --> 01:24:49,760
GERMANY 2, ALLIES NIL.

1179
01:24:49,800 --> 01:24:50,840
DAMN!

1180
01:25:00,920 --> 01:25:03,200
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

1181
01:25:20,680 --> 01:25:22,720
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1182
01:25:24,240 --> 01:25:26,200
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

1183
01:26:02,920 --> 01:26:04,440
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1184
01:26:42,360 --> 01:26:43,240
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1185
01:26:43,320 --> 01:26:44,320
PENALTY AREA.

1186
01:26:44,400 --> 01:26:46,720
THE REFEREE WILL PROBABLY
CALL A PENALTY KICK,

1187
01:26:46,800 --> 01:26:48,320
AND HE DOES.

1188
01:26:53,560 --> 01:26:54,680
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1189
01:26:54,720 --> 01:26:55,640
[YELLING IN GERMAN]

1190
01:26:55,680 --> 01:26:57,560
THIS IS THE FELLA HERE.

1191
01:26:57,600 --> 01:26:59,120
OH, COME ON!

1192
01:27:01,280 --> 01:27:03,960
THE REFEREE TRYING
TO SETTLE THEM DOWN.

1193
01:27:04,000 --> 01:27:05,400
THE CALL WILL REMAIN.

1194
01:27:05,440 --> 01:27:08,280
IT'LL BE A PENALTY KICK--
ONE ON ONE.

1195
01:27:08,320 --> 01:27:10,360
HATCH, THE GOALKEEPER.

1196
01:27:10,400 --> 01:27:12,760
HE'LL HAVE TO BE
ON HIS LINE.

1197
01:27:12,800 --> 01:27:14,680
HE TAKES A SHOT
AT YOU.

1198
01:27:14,720 --> 01:27:16,120
I'M SUPPOSED
TO STOP IT?

1199
01:27:16,160 --> 01:27:18,600
HE CANNOT MOVE
UNTIL THE BALL IS STRUCK.

1200
01:27:18,680 --> 01:27:20,120
YES, YES, INDEED.

1201
01:27:20,160 --> 01:27:23,160
GERMANY'S GREAT BAUMANN
WILL TAKE THE KICK.

1202
01:27:36,480 --> 01:27:38,080
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1203
01:27:42,320 --> 01:27:43,480
GOAL!

1204
01:27:43,520 --> 01:27:46,200
AND HE PUTS IT
BY HATCH,

1205
01:27:46,240 --> 01:27:49,000
AND IT'S 3-0 IN FAVOR
OF GERMANY.

1206
01:28:05,040 --> 01:28:06,880
THE ALLIES KICK OFF AGAIN.

1207
01:28:06,960 --> 01:28:08,800
IT'S RAY.
RAY TO FERNANDEZ.

1208
01:28:08,880 --> 01:28:10,240
FERNANDEZ BACK TO RAY.

1209
01:28:10,320 --> 01:28:12,640
WE HAVE SEEN
SOME VERY GOOD FOOTBALL.

1210
01:28:12,720 --> 01:28:14,720
VERY FORTUNATE FOR US,
INDEED.

1211
01:28:19,440 --> 01:28:21,280
BAUMANN MAKES
A BEAUTIFUL TACKLE,

1212
01:28:21,360 --> 01:28:22,240
DISPOSSESSES HIM,

1213
01:28:22,320 --> 01:28:25,040
AND THE GERMANS ARE AGAIN
ON THE ATTACK.

1214
01:28:41,120 --> 01:28:43,760
SO IT'S THE GERMANS 4-NIL.

1215
01:28:47,920 --> 01:28:49,240
STAY ON THE BLOODY LINE!

1216
01:28:49,280 --> 01:28:50,200
I MISSED.

1217
01:28:50,240 --> 01:28:51,640
STAY ON THE LINE!

1218
01:28:51,680 --> 01:28:54,080
WHEN THEY COME IN,
NARROW THE ANGLE.

1219
01:29:28,480 --> 01:29:29,760
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1220
01:29:43,080 --> 01:29:44,480
WE'LL PLAY 10 MEN.

1221
01:29:44,520 --> 01:29:46,160
I'LL GO FORWARD.

1222
01:29:46,240 --> 01:29:48,320
THIS AIN'T
GOING TO BE EASY.

1223
01:29:57,840 --> 01:29:59,600
WE'VE TAKEN ENOUGH!
LET'S GET 'EM!

1224
01:29:59,680 --> 01:30:01,880
THE ALLIES ARE PLAYING
